            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-19T17:00:00-04:00">July 19, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5954. From Cramer<note n="31" xml:id="d37fn1">Ambrose C. Cramer, Acting Director,
                        British Empire and Middle East Branch, Foreign Economic
                        Administration.</note> FEA for Blaisdell.<note n="32" xml:id="d37fn2">Thomas
                        C. Blaisdell, Chief of the United States Mission for Economic Affairs,
                        London.</note> Cox<note n="33" xml:id="d37fn3">Oscar Cox, Deputy
                        Administrator, Foreign Economic Administration.</note> discussed with Robert
                    Brand before latter’s departure for London FEA’s wish that British carefully
                    reconsider their previous objections to giving under Reverse Lend-Lease all Suez
                    Canal tolls paid by US. British have been told that FEA would be agreeable if
                    British secured participation by French. Records not complete but indicate
                    around 11½ million dollars expended by US from prior to 1943 through 1944 with
                    probability that 1945 charges will exceed 6 million. Please give your strong
                    support wherever appropriate. [Cramer.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
